3:17 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.pangea.ca/~grinch/ladun.jpg width=67 height=150></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   What does the future hold: Trakanon</span><hr size=1> In this thread, please discuss the problems with Trakanon under our old rotation.<br>
<br>
If you have suggestions on how to improve things, please also give them.<br>
<br>
The goal is to have, in 1 week's time, a concise list of problems with the Trakanon rotation, and potential solutions for them.<br>
<br>
REMEMBER!  The system in place must be good enough to EVERYONE that all are willing to abide by it.  Keep in mind that if there is no good solution, it means the rotation will likely become FCFS.  Also keep in mind that that FCFS is also a valid option, and CAN work if people are willing to respect each other. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#313532><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ujasiofneriak.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Jasi of Neriak</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Adventurer of Underfoot</span><br>  Posts: 40<br> <font color=#CC9900>(4/23/01 10:11:00 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://ang.mux.net/smjasi.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: What does the future hold: Trakanon</span><hr size=1> I honestly do not know enough about the Trakanon Rotation to state a clear opinion. I do know, though, that I cringe at the thought of FFA on such an important mob. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#414141><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uquemnwyndrunner.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Quemn Wyndrunner</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Assist Dammit!</span><br>  Posts: 748<br> <font color=#CC9900>(4/23/01 11:56:14 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: What does the future hold: Trakanon</span><hr size=1> you know im afraid to touch this one, but something needs to be done. i haven't thought of a good way of working this out, but this is what we need:<br>
<br>
trakanon to go down every time he is up<br>
more people knowledgable on trakanon so this can happen<br>
and fairness on sharing em<br>
<br>
i can see a FFA going on this, but i would like to find another possible answer. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#313532><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ugaennenfizzlewhiff.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Gaennen Fizzlewhiff</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Guardian of Underfoot</span><br>  Posts: 765<br> <font color=#CC9900>(4/23/01 12:00:22 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.jacksonville.net/~jshannon/images/Gaennen2-ico.GIF height=75 width=75></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: What does the future hold: Trakanon</span><hr size=1> FCFS <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#414141><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/utalanstoneheart.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Talan Stoneheart</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Holy Knight</span><br>  Posts: 327<br> <font color=#CC9900>(4/23/01 12:31:54 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: What does the future hold: Trakanon</span><hr size=1> FCFS, in my opinion... <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#313532><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uomenn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Omenn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Traveller of Underfoot</span><br>  Posts: 202<br> <font color=#CC9900>(4/23/01 1:24:59 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: What does the future hold: Trakanon</span><hr size=1> I can just see it now... three powerful guilds all setting up at the Seb entrance at the same time to take him down. And the shouting and complaints of who was there before.  Etc..<br>
<br>
Some of you may have been in chat with Oribi when the servers just started to go mad. She said that Brell was a great server.. one thing she noticed was that she never had to deal with Guilds fighting over eachother over spawns.. guess that will stop once Trak becomes FFA and more and more people get closer to 60.<br>
<br>
*sigh* <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#414141><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/bbrellserilis.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=duffer>Duffer</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/image/globalBlack.gif BORDER=0 HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>I'm a little teapot....</span><br>  Posts: 539<br> <font color=#CC9900>(4/23/01 1:48:24 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: What does the future hold: Trakanon</span><hr size=1> <br>
Hrm,<br>
<br>
I was just talking to a friend of mine who plays on another server.  On that server, three guilds monopolize Trak...<br>
<br>
BUT, what the guilds have instituted is that every 4th Trak spawn is &quot;open&quot; ... if another guild gets in and kills him, great!  Once a guild has killed Trak 3x on the &quot;open spawn&quot; then that guild gets added to the rotation, and every 5th Trak is now open season.  He belongs to a guild who just killed them for the third time, and just got put on the rotation.<br>
<br>
I haven't had much time to digest this, but my first thought is that it seems like it works pretty well on a &quot;guild only&quot; basis... the problem is one of the strenghs of Brell is our &quot;we are all members of the same community&quot; mentality.  But perhaps some similar modified system could be put in place in order to prevent total fcfs on this dragon.<br>
<br>
Duffer <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#313532><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uomenn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Omenn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Traveller of Underfoot</span><br>  Posts: 204<br> <font color=#CC9900>(4/23/01 2:37:02 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: What does the future hold: Trakanon</span><hr size=1> If I were to chose between fcfs and Duffer's friend's server's system.. I would go with Duffer.  Sounds good. If you can prove you can kill him, then you should be added to the list. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#414141><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/utwiggietymberwolf.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Twiggie Tymberwolf</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Guardian of Underfoot</span><br>  Posts: 782<br> <font color=#CC9900>(4/23/01 3:32:39 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: What does the future hold: Trakanon</span><hr size=1> FCFS in my opinion for this spawn.  Lock the sign ups and when all on it have finished then its FCFS.<br>
<br>
He's only needed for VP keys and the ones that could go to VP and not get slaughtered are the ones who would be able to kill him on a FCFS system.  It will just end up like VS list if the list is kept.  More and more guilds will sign up till you have 30+ guilds on the list.  The fighting over this will be worse than VS since guilds will have to wait 10 weeks at a time just to get a few teeth.  It will takes months and months to get enough teeth for the guild.   With FCFS the strongest, and the ones suited to be in VP, will get their keys first and then not bother with him anymore, and that will allow the next tier to move up and take him down.<br>
<br>
BP's he drops aren't really needed since you can get equal or better BP's in PoG or any of the Velious quests or even drops in West Wastes.<br>
<br>
<br>
The top guilds shared him before he was scheduled, they will do the same if he is removed.  I doubt Watchers and SR will show up in the zone and fight over him.  They just did joint Dain and VS raids so obviously they know how and do talk with each other and work things out in game.<br>
<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#313532><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ujasiofneriak.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Jasi of Neriak</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Adventurer of Underfoot</span><br>  Posts: 42<br> <font color=#CC9900>(4/23/01 11:48:34 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://ang.mux.net/smjasi.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: What does the future hold: Trakanon</span><hr size=1> I don't think you can really say that the BP's are no longer necessary. While there are things from Velious that are better, it doesn't mean everyone has access to them. Getting a Mylar (uhm.. Milo's Car? My Low Car? OH! Mrylokar ;) BP would make me have a high for an entire week straight. There may not be as much value as there once was, but they're still important. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#414141><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ukallikamerov.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kalli Kamerov</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Protector of Underfoot</span><br>  Posts: 471<br> <font color=#CC9900>(4/24/01 12:06:56 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://images.honesty.com/imagedata/h/895/90/28959015.jpg width = 135 height = 184></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: What does the future hold: Trakanon</span><hr size=1> Donal's BP is still one of the most powerful items a cleric can have, Dhark's has easily upped the killing power of our groups and pull team for hate / fear more than any other item we've seen.  (though I'd put the cleric epic as more useful in all, especially for raids)<br>
<br>
The Velious BP has what? Mark of Karn? or Super nerfed Celestial Elixir, not even in the same Ballpark for usefulness.<br>
<br>
Unless I'm mistaken, Trak's a 3 day spawn, with 2 indy's and (at least) 1 small guild out of 14 on the list currently.  It's fairly obvious that guilds are not rushing to jump onto this list at any high rate of speed (wasn't it 7 guilds in november?), and the turn over rate is still under 2 months even in a worst case scenario.  <br>
<br>
Personally, I'd like to see, if a change is warranted, a list system, much like Adune's 18 person idea from awhile back, but a bit harsher, perhaps for Trak requiring 24 people 53(55?)+ and any guild represented by the people on the list counts as a joint raid, ie, if guild A produced 12 people, pulled 6 from guild B, 3 from guild C, 2 from guild D, and 1 from guild E to form their list, that it be considered a joint  Guild's A-E raid.  <br>
<br>
That alone should chop down the list a bit, as well as keeping any signups honest.<br>
<br>
Kalli Kamerov<br>
55th Enchantress<br>
Poison Arrow. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#313532><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/usupasteve.showPublicProfile?language=EN>supasteve</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Adventurer of Underfoot</span><br>  Posts: 28<br> <font color=#CC9900>(4/25/01 9:17:19 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: What does the future hold: Trakanon</span><hr size=1> i have just recently gotten to the lvl that i can do trak and i have been working on my pr gear. i have never done trak but i would like to, i dont think that i would be able to ever help kill him if he was fcfs because i am afraid that i wouldnt be able to sign up on a list beforehand and i doubt that i would be included in a spur of the moment raid. i dont know anything about the trak rotation and who was killing him lately but when deciding on the system please try to make it so people who are high enough to kill him but guilds arent high enough yet have a chance.<br>
kaervak darkheart 56 shadowknight<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#414141><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/usingollo.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Singollo</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Traveller of Underfoot</span><br>  Posts: 162<br> <font color=#CC9900>(4/25/01 11:15:41 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: What does the future hold: Trakanon</span><hr size=1> If it aint broke, dont fix it.<br>
<br>
Not that in the future, sometime, we may need to revise it or just go fcfs.<br>
But for now, if there isnt a problem with him, why try to add more confusion to the game for people? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#313532><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/useriana.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Seriana</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Adventurer of Underfoot</span><br>  Posts: 71<br> <font color=#CC9900>(4/26/01 8:06:19 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: What does the future hold: Trakanon</span><hr size=1> What was wrong with the Trakanon rotation?<br>
<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#414141><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uhalarus.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Halarus</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Adventurer of Underfoot</span><br>  Posts: 98<br> <font color=#CC9900>(4/26/01 10:09:10 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: What does the future hold: Trakanon</span><hr size=1> Looking at the current list there doesn't seem to be a problem.  There's currently 14 people on the rotation.  Outside of a couple indy's and MAYBE 1 or 2 guilds, it looks like the majority of people on the list will be able to take him down with ease, and with a majority of the participants being from their own guild.  While the &quot;ubers&quot; might have to wait a little longer (1 to 1.5 months) to kill him, that's the consequence of an aging population under a rotation system.  If it gets above 25 people, or if people start signing up that honestly wouldn't have a shot at him, then I'd say do something.  It's nowhere near out of hand at the moment, so I'd say let it be.   <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#313532><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/usaphdia.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Saphdia</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Guardian of Underfoot</span><br>  Posts: 2473<br> <font color=#CC9900>(4/26/01 10:37:33 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: What does the future hold: Trakanon</span><hr size=1> I think trak should be handled like what adun mentioned in the vox/nagafen thread.  Take off the rotation...let's get a forum in here for the here and now..not to go past one week.<br>
<br>
People say this hasn't become as bad as VS.  Newsflash guys..why would we want to even build up to that again?  We nearly lost (still in debate we'll see who really abides by it once this is set up) the reservation system over VS.  Why even set ourselves up for another blow up on trak later?  more and more people are growing up to do it and already there is a 1 month wait.  I think lock the current reservation on trak and then start with the new forum that encourages people work together. If for some reason this doesn't work, then things can always be brought up for change.  I'd say to add criteria in order to even participate in the forum but something tells me that would just bring on more fights as to what criteria we'd use.  I think most people that have even signed up for the planes that obviously had no clue, ended up not signing up for them again.  They learned how hard it really was. <br>
<br>
Saph  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#414141><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uadunofbrell.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Adun of Brell</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/image/globalBlack.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Burn the Witch! [Mod]</span><br>  Posts: 1808<br> <font color=#CC9900>(4/26/01 11:20:33 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.pangea.ca/~grinch/ladun.jpg width=67 height=150></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: What does the future hold: Trakanon</span><hr size=1> Woot!  Hell freezes over.  Saph &amp; Adun agree on something.  Details at 11.<br>
<br>
Just wanted to drop my jaw.<br>
<br>
Consensus from the guild meet was: Yes, most prefer Trak on Rotation.  But all agreed that there had to be some kind of limit, or requirement to get on the trak list.  Nobody wants to see a VS kind of list on any other rotated mob ever again on Brell. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#313532><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/usaphdia.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Saphdia</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Guardian of Underfoot</span><br>  Posts: 2480<br> <font color=#CC9900>(4/26/01 12:27:13 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: What does the future hold: Trakanon</span><hr size=1> After 3.5 - 4 hours Pharma and I left the meeting.<br>
<br>
We observed on trak that there was still contention around what to do with trak...not that there was a consensus.<br>
<br>
Also, no where was it ever even given as an idea an alternate way of doing things other than a list.  I'm sure you may have had people's attention with that.  If this came up, it was due after the 3.5 - 4 hours that we stayed.<br>
<br>
I guarantee you if you go back to a list type setting you will have problems and why would you want to repeat such a  thing?<br>
<br>
Saph <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#414141><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uklugsvear.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Klug Svear</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Adventurer of Underfoot</span><br>  Posts: 78<br> <font color=#CC9900>(4/26/01 1:55:58 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://members.home.net/marklefebvre/Klug.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: What does the future hold: Trakanon</span><hr size=1> *These are my opinions, not necessarily those of the Guild I belong to*<br>
<br>
I belong to a Guild that has 16 members. We are all friends, and almost all of us have been playing on Brell for over a year. We all have characters over level 50 (with 2 exceptions).<br>
<br>
We have successfully organized and completed raids of 4 or more groups, in such various places as Hate, Fear, the Hole, and CoM. These raids were supplemented by friends of ours from other Guilds, as well as a few folk who signed up in the hope they would go.<br>
<br>
In about 2 months, we will all be of sufficient level and gear to take down Trakanon. We will accomplish this by supplementing our raid with numerous friends, and a few folk who sign up in the hope they can go.<br>
<br>
Why do we want to take down Trak? Well, regardless of Twiggies opinion, many of our members place great value on the BP he drops. By hosting the raid as a Guild, we can insure that our idea of loot fairness is enforced, we can insure that all of our members can attend, and we get the thrill of leading a raid on a Dragon (something I happen to enjoy). Our odds of obtaining a Trak BP for a Guild member are increased, by virtue of having all of our members attending the raid.<br>
<br>
It would take me about a week to organize a 6 person raid, given the size of our Guild, and all of our friend's schedules. And, the extra time to prepare, do research and planning, etc. improves our odds of success. Having open sign-ups, as we do now for Dragons and Planes, allows me to fill any class/lvl gaps I may have.<br>
<br>
So, if Trak is FCFS (FFA, same difference, trust me, I have chars on other servers) who will be able to kill him? Only those few Guilds that have around 25 or so level 55+ members (the rest can be recruited on spur of the moment).<br>
<br>
Truthfully, without some type of list, Epiphany will never be able to host a Trak raid.<br>
<br>
My personal vote on this matter is to leave the schedule as is.<br>
<br>
Respectfully,<br>
Klug Svear<br>
54th Barbarian Champion<br>
Epiphany<br>
<br>
