Adun's proposal on the vox/naggy thread made allowances for it not to be fcfs.  Just because we don't do the list way doesn't mean it still has to be fcfs.  I am too lazy to go back to vox/naggy thread to pull it out but the gist of adun's proposal as I understand it is that weekly people can sign up to take trak under a &quot;forum&quot;..and then they work together.  <br>
<br>
So Epiphany under whatever rules for this forum says..hey..we have about 15 members ready to take trak down this week and we have 5 friends or so.  We will need another 10 to 15, what guild would like to join us? Or maybe you go ahead and see someone else is interested and you say..hey let's split it.  It is just for that raid.  Something has to give in the system on these &quot;reservable&quot; mobs.  Let's look at my guild for example.  If we signed up for a trak raid and we saw 2 other guilds that had the same interest, I'd like to think that we would work it out with them.  We'd choose from our guild who would go...and the same thing from the other two if they wanted to &quot;share&quot; that week.  We obviously wouldn't even bring friends if we were going to discount guildmates because our guildmates will always come first. <br>
<br>
This way you don't necessarily have to wait a whole month to go...you may end up..but you may not.  This clearly gets rid of lists that last 10 months and promotes unity between the guilds in the community.  You can sure tell who is trying to monopolize the spawn...it should be tracked.<br>
<br>
I think no one would disagree that trak is ok right now..but it will become bad as people grow up in the game and that isn't too far off into the future.  We have seen this list idea hurt the vox/naggy as well as VS.  By the time vox/naggy come around, some guilds have even outgrown the mob and some other guilds are just going through the motions because their name is up there even though the person who had passion to do such a raid is gone from the guild.  That guild wouldn't have probably even remained on the rotation if it were a current weekly thing.<br>
<br>
Why I ask would anyone want to do it for trak just because?  The end result has been proven that with a list system, you will sign up and you MAY get to it in 8 months.  Doesn't sound right to me.  Let's come up with some forum rules that go by weekly only and work out something. <br>
<br>
Believe me Klug, i used to think the list idea was the most fair.  Since I've read a lot of people's post (some with a grain of salt), I am starting to see the frustration they are feeling. I myself am not necessarily frustrated but if we allow a system to be too frustrating, it won't be in business for long. <br>
